{"insight":"A useful ladder must be left behind","plainSummary":"A path may ask us to trust a tool until the next step teaches us to let it go.","atAGlance":"Good training often gives the heart one thing to hold. Then it teaches the hand to open. The danger is keeping the tool after its work is done. A true path shows both the permission and the release.","match":["licensed training mistake"],"tags":["practice","release","humility","discernment"]}
